'''Alan Steve Minda García''' (born 14 May 2003) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[Clube Atlético Mineiro|Atlético Mineiro]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Club career==
===Independiente del Valle===
Born in [[Esmeraldas, Ecuador|Esmeraldas]], Minda joined [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]]'s youth setup in 2016, from [[C.D. El Nacional|El Nacional]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lacancha.movix.com/alan-minda-se-formo-en-el-nacional-pero-brilla-en-independiente/|title=Alan Minda se formó en El Nacional, pero brilla en Independiente|trans-title=Alan Minda was formed at El Nacional, but shines at Independiente|publisher=La Cancha|language=es|date=6 September 2022|accessdate=1 June 2023}}</ref> After making his senior debut with the reserve team [[C.D. Independiente Juniors|Independiente Juniors]] in the 2020 [[Ecuadorian Serie B]], he made his debut with the main squad on 22 May 2021, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[José Hurtado (footballer)|José Hurtado]] in a 3–0 [[Ecuadorian Serie A]] home win over [[Guayaquil City F.C.|Guayaquil City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lacancha.movix.com/independiente-del-valle-goleo-a-guayaquil-city-y-esta-a-un-paso-del-liderazgo-de-la-ligapro/|title=Independiente del Valle goleó a Guayaquil City y está a un paso del liderazgo de la LigaPro|trans-title=Independiente del Valle thrashed Guayaquil City and is one step away from the leadership of the ''LigaPro''|publisher=La Cancha|language=es|date=22 May 2021|accessdate=1 June 2023}}</ref>

Minda scored his first professional goal on 1 August 2021, netting his team's third in a 4–0 home routing of [[C.S.D. Macará|Macará]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.benditofutbol.com/independiente-del-valle/independiente-goleada-macara-ligapro-sangolqui.html|title=Independiente del Valle somete al Macará y se mantiene en la cima|trans-title=Independiente del Valle subdue Macará and remain in the top half|publisher=Bendito Fútbol|language=es|date=1 August 2021|accessdate=1 June 2023}}</ref> After featuring regularly, he suffered a serious [[knee]] injury in December,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mifutbolecuador.futbol/2021/12/02/alan-minda-fue-operado-en-espana-gracias-a-la-hermandad-de-su-equipo-con-el-cd-numancia%EF%BF%BC/|title=Alan Minda fue operado en España gracias a la hermandad de su equipo con el CD Numancia|trans-title=Alan Minda was operated in Spain thanks to the partnership of his team with CD Numancia|publisher=Mi Fútbol Ecuatoriano|language=es|date=2 December 2021|accessdate=1 June 2023}}</ref> being sidelined for several months of the 2022 season.

On 18 April 2023, on his [[Copa Libertadores]] debut, Minda scored ''IDV''{{'}}s second in a 2–0 win over [[Liverpool F.C. (Montevideo)|Liverpool Montevideo]]; by doing so, he became the quickest to score for the club after coming on a substitute in the tournament's history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metroecuador.com.ec/deportes/2023/04/19/alan-minda-marco-con-independiente-del-valle-y-establecio-un-record-en-copa-libertadores/|title=¡Quedará en la historia! Alan Minda marcó con Independiente del Valle y estableció un récord en Copa Libertadores|trans-title=Will go down in history! Alan Minda scored with Independiente del Valle and set a record in the Copa Libertadores|publisher=Metro|language=es|date=19 April 2023|accessdate=1 June 2023}}</ref>

===Cercle Brugge===
On 12 July 2023, Belgian club [[Cercle Brugge K.S.V.|Cercle Brugge]] announced the signing of Minda on a five-year contract,<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 July 2023 |title=Alan Minda naar Cercle Brugge |trans-title=Alan minda joins Cercle Brugge |url=https://cerclebrugge.be/en/news/articles/Minda2028 |access-date=12 July 2023 |publisher=Cercle Brugge KSV |language=en}}</ref> for a reported fee of around [[Euro|€]]2 million.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=12 July 2023 |title=Atacante formado no Del Valle é anunciado por clube europeu |trans-title=Attacker trained in Del Valle is announced by European club |url=https://futebolatino.lance.com.br/atacante-formado-no-del-valle-e-anunciado-por-clube-europeu/ |access-date=12 July 2023 |website=Futebol Latino |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

===Atlético Mineiro===
On 6 January 2026, Brazilian club [[Clube Atlético Mineiro|Atlético Mineiro]] announced an agreement in principle to sign Minda.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=6 January 2026 |title=Comunicado - Alan Minda |trans-title=Statement - Alan Minda |url=https://atletico.com.br/comunicado-alan-minda/ |access-date=6 January 2026 |website=Clube Atlético Mineiro |language=pt-BR}}</ref> On 14 January, the deal was confirmed and he signed a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=14 January 2026 |title=Alan Minda é do Galo! |trans-title=Alan Minda to Galo! |url=https://atletico.com.br/minda-e-do-galo/ |access-date=14 January 2026 |website=Clube Atlético Mineiro |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

==International career==
Minda made his debut for the [[Ecuador national under-20 football team|Ecuador national under-20 team]] in November 2022, in two friendlies against [[Colombia national under-20 football team|Colombia]]. He was also included in the side's squads for the [[2023 South American U-20 Championship]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elcomercio.com/deportes/futbol/convocatoria-ecuador-sudamericano-sub20-futbol.html|title=La convocatoria de Ecuador para el Sudamericano Sub 20 quedó definida|trans-title=Ecuador's squad for the South American Sub 20 was defined|publisher=[[El Comercio (Ecuador)|El Comercio]]|date=5 January 2023|language=es}}</ref> and the [[2023 FIFA U-20 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ecuavisa.com/deportes/futbol-internacional/mundial-sub-20-estos-son-los-convocados-de-ecuador-que-disputaran-este-torneo-CG5091455|title=Mundial Sub 20: Estos son los convocados de Ecuador que disputaran este torneo|trans-title=U-20 World Cup: These are the called up players of Ecuador who will play this tournament|publisher=[[Ecuavisa]]|first=Fernando|last=Guevara|date=9 May 2023|language=es}}</ref>

Minda made his debut for the senior [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]] on 22 March 2024 in a friendly against [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/698420/guatemala-ecuador|title=Ecuador v Guatemala game report|date=22 March 2024}}</ref>

